lisa-design:
- SUPERSEDES the earlier "ProfileComplianceView shows an Inherited tile pinned at 0 — accepted trade-off" decision (human-directed in PR #285 review by gusfcarvalho): ComplianceProgressPanel now HIDES the Inherited summary tile in profile scope, via `showInheritedTile = !!sspId || (summary.inherited ?? 0) > 0`, and switches the tiles grid md:grid-cols-6 ↔ md:grid-cols-5 to match. The tile still shows in SSP scope even at 0 (there "Inherited: 0" is real information). The overall-bar purple segment + legend are unchanged (zero-width in profile scope, harmless).
- CompliancePostureWidget (dashboard) now renders the purple `inherited` bar segment too (was only 3 of 4 buckets). It is fed by the PROFILE endpoint so inherited is always 0 today (segment zero-width); rendered defensively so the bar stays gap-free if ever repointed at SSP-scoped data. Deliberately NO numeric Inherited tile added there — that would reintroduce the permanently-zero-tile problem just removed from the panel.
